<emphasis id="5EABFD32E12B6CC12722E985988888AD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Estinogena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="41986F3314D80D829EC836262123C6A6" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Phylogenetic tree of Penicillium section Gracilenta based on ML analysis obtained by RAxML inferred from the combined tub 2, cmdA, ITS, and rpb 2 loci. Branch lengths are proportional to phylogenetic distance. Bootstrap support values / Bayesian posterior probability scores above 70 % / 0.95 are indicated on the nodes. Bold branches indicate bs / pp values 100 / 1. The tree is rooted to P. abidjanum CBS 246.67. The name in red is the new species described in this study. T = Ex-type strain." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.86.73861.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640606" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">7</figureCitation>
). This species shows morphological attributes of the series based on its type 
<taxonomicName id="86D0481FADE0037B9F7DF6B8F476D5C4" genus="P." lsidName="P. estinogenum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="estinogenum">
<emphasis id="127AC58368DEF049D35CEDF68FB91448" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. estinogenum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, namely that both have symmetrically appressed biverticillate conidiophores with rough-walled stipes (
<bibRefCitation id="094D62A2066921BC91CBFB03D680EAAC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.05.002" author="Houbraken, J" journalOrPublisher="Studies in Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="5 - 169" refId="B39" refString="Houbraken, J, Kocsube, S, Visagie, CM, Yilmaz, N, Wang, XC, Meijer, M, Kraak, B, Hubka, V, Bensch, K, Samson, RA, Frisvad, JC, 2020. Classification of Aspergillus, Penicillium, Talaromyces and related genera (Eurotiales): an overview of families, genera, subgenera, sections, series and species. Studies in Mycology 95: 5 - 169, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.05.002" title="Classification of Aspergillus, Penicillium, Talaromyces and related genera (Eurotiales): an overview of families, genera, subgenera, sections, series and species." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.05.002" volume="95" year="2020">Houbraken et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName id="1340EE73CD05DEF51FD2A3364E0C2136" genus="P." lsidName="P. guarroi" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="guarroi">
<emphasis id="8FE7C3ED146A90029EDA879292C98923" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. guarroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly differs from 
<taxonomicName id="C86772E019BAC5C2FEC778171C21361E" genus="P." lsidName="P. estinogenum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="estinogenum">
<emphasis id="BD5D22DA9424070D80FF12AD17A3DA8E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. estinogenum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by producing strictly smooth-walled globose conidia, which are ellipsoidal to ovate and with smooth to finely roughened walls in the latter (
<bibRefCitation id="FD97702BA191193EEADE9A7454FDD80B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2323/jgam.2.1" author="Abe, S" journalOrPublisher="The Journal of General and Applied Microbiology" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="1 - 194" refId="B2" refString="Abe, S, 1956. Studies on the classification of the Penicillia. The Journal of General and Applied Microbiology 2: 1 - 194, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2323/jgam.2.1" title="Studies on the classification of the Penicillia." url="https://doi.org/10.2323/jgam.2.1" volume="2" year="1956">Abe 1956</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="9E8C4E5C82CAED18822FCEE6CC2FC51F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.05.002" author="Houbraken, J" journalOrPublisher="Studies in Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="5 - 169" refId="B39" refString="Houbraken, J, Kocsube, S, Visagie, CM, Yilmaz, N, Wang, XC, Meijer, M, Kraak, B, Hubka, V, Bensch, K, Samson, RA, Frisvad, JC, 2020. Classification of Aspergillus, Penicillium, Talaromyces and related genera (Eurotiales): an overview of families, genera, subgenera, sections, series and species. Studies in Mycology 95: 5 - 169, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.05.002" title="Classification of Aspergillus, Penicillium, Talaromyces and related genera (Eurotiales): an overview of families, genera, subgenera, sections, series and species." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.05.002" volume="95" year="2020">Houbraken et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In addition to their phylogenetic distance, other members of 
<taxonomicName id="BD7702DEC6715445D8C49865F4C70056" authority="Gracilenta" genus="P." lsidName="subsp. section" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="section" section="Gracilenta" species="estinogenum" subSpecies="section">section Gracilenta</taxonomicName>
(i.e., series 
<taxonomicName id="CB4CAE78C20DC86608486765DD90B121" genus="P." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="series" series="Gracilenta">
<emphasis id="261E8FAD232CED87104690BD5A01AF18" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Gracilenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1C30096844293E8AC07BA897DC89D561" genus="Macrosclerotiorum" lsidName="Macrosclerotiorum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9BAF5BE6B8DA7C84FED48EE8CD4754DD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Macrosclerotiorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) can be differentiated morphologically by the production of monoverticillate conidiophores and the lack of growth at 37 °C, with the exception of 
<taxonomicName id="96773D2706E8DDE9BCE5C1E8198D9DC3" genus="P." lsidName="P. apimei" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="apimei">
<emphasis id="D185A0E9F188BAF36027DCBBF6E4A8B0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. apimei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9B1B406AB3ECDC26F8249770B4238430" genus="P." lsidName="P. aquaticum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="aquaticum">
<emphasis id="FA4EFE99E13FB1568938E8E32A208F3E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. aquaticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are able to grow at this temperature (
<bibRefCitation id="B7D94FB1A6A7946E47EB2A1FF74A7568" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10482-018-1081-1" author="Barbosa, RN" journalOrPublisher="Antonie van Leeuwenhoek" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="1883 - 1912" refId="B6" refString="Barbosa, RN, Bezerra, JD, Souza-Motta, CM, Frisvad, JC, Samson, RA, Oliveira, NT, Houbraken, J, 2018. New Penicillium and Talaromyces species from honey, pollen and nests of stingless bees. Antonie van Leeuwenhoek 111: 1883 - 1912, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s10482-018-1081-1" title="New Penicillium and Talaromyces species from honey, pollen and nests of stingless bees." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10482-018-1081-1" volume="111" year="2018">Barbosa et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8FEBA71D6A447A2488281F0435D0DEAD" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.05.002" author="Houbraken, J" journalOrPublisher="Studies in Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="5 - 169" refId="B39" refString="Houbraken, J, Kocsube, S, Visagie, CM, Yilmaz, N, Wang, XC, Meijer, M, Kraak, B, Hubka, V, Bensch, K, Samson, RA, Frisvad, JC, 2020. Classification of Aspergillus, Penicillium, Talaromyces and related genera (Eurotiales): an overview of families, genera, subgenera, sections, series and species. Studies in Mycology 95: 5 - 169, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.05.002" title="Classification of Aspergillus, Penicillium, Talaromyces and related genera (Eurotiales): an overview of families, genera, subgenera, sections, series and species." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.05.002" volume="95" year="2020">Houbraken et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="1201EA59158B01DBF523A30CA8BE07D5" authorityName="Torres-Garcia, Gene and Dania Garcia" authorityYear="2022" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Aspergillaceae" genus="Penicillium" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Penicillium guarroi" order="Eurotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="guarroi">
<emphasis id="40B94B41C96B658BFBA07F7C80162C14" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Penicillium guarroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was unable to grow at 37 °C, but it shows a maximum temperature for growth at 35 °C (4-5 mm), like other members in the section (i.e., 
<taxonomicName id="688873F22EB7D8BE49C68954A9216C22" genus="P." lsidName="P. macrosclerotiorum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="macrosclerotiorum">
<emphasis id="D6A98A0403D6ABF23D3348F19D76BCCA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. macrosclerotiorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9347EEFB464E1B0F591E2171A5ED33F7" genus="P." lsidName="P. angustiporcatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="angustiporcatum">
<emphasis id="0E6B7A9E8DE23C0F7CB207B66AF8EFCE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. angustiporcatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9880C91FD4DA944A8F13A41094FAF71E" genus="P." lsidName="P. gracilentum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="gracilentum">
<emphasis id="17EE61BC6DDC48E3865EBF646146FA94" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. gracilentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="5A4591A22C4964B1EC5969D2C1087146" genus="P." lsidName="P. estinogenum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="estinogenum">
<emphasis id="5B7394F16EC05E5A3034BDECF272676D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. estinogenum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
